AGI - The deputy attorney general asked the Court of Cassation to confirm the sentence to 27 years in prison for Valerio del Grosso accused of being the material executor of the murder of Luca Sacchi, the personal trainer killed on 24 October 2019 in front of a pub in the Appio area, in the Capital. The representative of the public prosecutor also called for confirmation of the three-year sentence for Anastasiya Kylemnyk - at the time of the victim's fiancée -, for the only facts of drugs, and a process in appeal bis to Paolo Pirino and Marcello De Propris, to reevaluate the penalty discount granted them in the first appeal process. Pirino and De Propris were first sentenced to 25 years for murder contest but in the second degree judgment they had benefited from a 14-year-old and 8-month prison discount. The prosecution therefore asked to accept the use of the general prosecutor to reevaluate the granting of that penalty reduction.
